{"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","title":"centerOffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159","fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h"},"symbolKind":"property"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"dx","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the left.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","title":"MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotationView"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true},{"text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object that corresponds to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"title":"centerOffset","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNAnnotation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","role":"symbol"}}}